			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	It appears that deductions are committed to the database at the point of action.  When the turn rolls back because of a server glitch, the bidding starts where it left off the previous turn and your bid for the current turn is lost and since your bid had already been deducted from the database, it is also gone.  THIS NEEDS TO BE FIXED!!!!!  I haven't figured out an exploit in PP yet, but I'm sure it is there somewhere just as it is in fleets.<br />
<br />
Perhaps if the Black Market bids are also committed to the database at the point of action?  This should go for all investments as well if they aren't that way already.<br />
<br />
I'm sure that this opens up a glitch of somekind with a rapid succession reset worm, but I haven't figured it out yet.  Being able to bribe multiple times in the same turn to get to perfect subject in a matter of minutes perhaps?			   <P align=right></P>
